  "text": "An alternative possibility to be considered is that by itself, CREB activation can produce spines, but the extent of this action depends on the pattern of CREB activation rather than on the absolute level of activated CREB. For example, it was recently found that a cyclic elevation of intracellular calcium can enhance gene expression differentially in a way that is distinct from that produced by a continuous rise in [Ca] i [CITATION_1] [Ca] , and its subsequent effect on CREB activation, its duration, and magnitude will determine the ability of CREB to cause the formation of dendritic spines.",
